        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 10:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1015 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Baileys Park, or near
Hawkinsville, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dubois, Cochran, Hawkinsville, Empire, Mobley Crossing, Hartford,
Pulaski State Prison, Baileys Park, and Ocmulgee Banks.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
